== Etymology ==
Karimnagar was originally called ''Elagandala''.<ref>{{cite web|title=District Census Handbook – Adilabad|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/2801_PART_B_DCHB_ADILABAD.pdf|website=Census of India|accessdate=20 November 2015|page=9|format=PDF}}</ref> Later Kannada kingdoms such as Western Chalukyas ruled it. It was part of the great [[Satavahana Empire]]. Later, the ruling [[Nizam of Hyderabad|Nizams]] of Hyderabad changed the name to ''Karimnagar'', derived from the name of ''Shahenshah E Karimnagar Syed Kareemullah Shah Quadri''.
